|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100130021913/http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/content/abstract/308/5724/1034
|dead-url=no
}}</ref>

莎拉·提胥可夫率領的廣大非洲的遺傳多樣性研究團隊，從113個不同人群的採樣當中，發現[[布希曼人|布希曼人]]具有最大的遺傳多樣性，這使得他們成為14個{{link-en|人類基因叢集|Human genetic clustering}}的其中一個。這項研究也定位了非洲西南部現代人類遷移的源頭，接近[[納米比亞|納米比亞]]和[[安哥拉|安哥拉]]海岸。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/8027269.stm |title=Africa's genetic secrets unlocked |date=May 1, 2009 |last=Gill |first=Victoria |work=[[BBC_News|BBC News]] |accessdate=June 8, 2011 |archive-date=2009-07-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090701001654/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/8027269.stm |dead-url=no }} the results were published in the online edition of the journal ''Science''.</ref>

根據人類學家和考古學家所採用的[[多峇巨災理論|多峇巨災理論]]，大約在距今七萬年前，印尼[[蘇門答臘|蘇門答臘]]島的[[多巴湖|多峇湖]]發生一場[[超級火山|超級火山噴發]]，造成了全球性的後果，<ref>"[http://www.bbc.co.uk/sn/prehistoric_life/human/human_evolution/new_batch1.shtml The new batch - 150,000 years ago] {{Wayback|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/sn/prehistoric_life/human/human_evolution/new_batch1.shtml |date=20060326004611 }}". BBC - Science & Nature - The evolution of man.</ref>致使當時的大多數人死亡，並創造出一個[[種群瓶頸|種群瓶頸]]，影響現今所有人類的基因遺傳。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/2975862.stm|title=When humans faced extinction|publisher=BBC|date=2003-06-09|accessdate=2007-01-05|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5uQpdbri7?url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/2975862.stm|archivedate=2010-11-22|deadurl=no}}</ref>

===多地起源模型===
{{Main|多地起源说}}

「多地起源模型」是一種「解釋人類演化的模型」，由沃波夫（Milford H. Wolpoff）於1988年提出。<ref name="multiregional">
{{cite journal
|last=Wolpoff
|first=MH
|coauthors={{link-en|Hawks J|John D. Hawks}}, Caspari R
|year=2000
|title=Multiregional, not multiple origins
|journal=Am J Phys Anthropol
|volume=112
|issue=1
|pages=129–36
|url=http://www3.interscience.wiley.com/journal/71008905/abstract
|doi=10.1002/(SICI)1096-8644(200005)112:1<129::AID-AJPA11>3.0.CO;2-K
|pmid=10766948
}}{{Dead link|date=2019年5月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}
</ref><ref name="Wolpoff1988">{{cite journal
| doi=10.1126/science.3136545
| last=Wolpoff
| first=MH
| coauthors=JN Spuhler, FH Smith, J Radovcic, G Pope, DW Frayer, R Eckhardt, and G Clark
| year=1988
| title=Modern Human Origins
| journal=Science
| volume=241
| issue=4867
| pages=772–4
| url=http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/pdf_extract/241/4867/772
| pmid=3136545
| access-date=2011-11-10
| archive-date=2015-09-24
| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924135546/http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/pdf_extract/241/4867/772
| dead-url=no
}}</ref>多區域演化的觀點主張，人類演化是從距今250萬年前的[[更新世|更新世]]開始，直到現在，一直維持著單一的、連續的[[人類|人類]]物種，在世界各地演化成為現代智人。依據多區域假設，化石及[[基因體|基因體]]資料是說明全球性人類演化的證據，這與最近由晚近非洲起源說所假定的[[物種形成|物種形成]]過程相矛盾。[[理查德·李奇|理查德·李奇]]認為化石證據並不充足，無法解決這個爭論。
<ref name="RLeakey">{{cite book|last=Leakey|first=Richard|title=The Origin of Humankind|url=https://archive.org/details/originofhumankin00leak|publisher=Basic Books|location=New York, NY|year=1994|series=Science Masters Series|pages=[https://archive.org/details/originofhumankin00leak/page/87 87]–89|isbn=978-0-465-05313-1}}</ref>對於[[Y染色體|Y染色體]]及[[粒線體DNA|粒線體DNA]]的[[單倍群|單倍群]]研究已大大支持一個晚近的非洲起源。<ref>{{cite journal |author=Jorde LB, Bamshad M, Rogers AR |title=Using mitochondrial and nuclear DNA markers to reconstruct human evolution |journal=Bioessays |volume=20 |issue=2 |pages=126–36 |pmid=9631658 |doi=10.1002/(SICI)1521-1878(199802)20:2<126::AID-BIES5>3.0.CO;2-R |date=February 1998}}</ref>來自[[常染色體|常染色體]]DNA的證據也支持晚近非洲起源的可能性。然而，某些研究顯示，古智人（Archaic Homo sapiens）的遺傳成分也有可能摻雜在當代人類當中。<ref name="Wall, J. D. 2009 1823">{{Cite journal
| doi = 10.1093/molbev/msp096
| pmc = 2734152
| title = Detecting Ancient Admixture and Estimating Demographic Parameters in Multiple Human Populations
| url = https://archive.org/details/sim_molecular-biology-and-evolution_2009-08_26_8/page/1823
| pmid = 19420049
| year = 2009
| author = Wall, J. D.
| journal = Molecular Biology and Evolution
| volume = 26
| issue = 8
| last2 = Lohmueller
| first2 = K. E.
| last3 = Plagnol
| first3 = V.
| pages = 1823–7 / 1823
}}</ref>最近關於[[尼安德塔人|尼安德塔人]]<ref>Green RE, Krause J, et al. A draft sequence of the Neandertal genome. Science. 2010 May 7;328 (5979):710-22. PMID 20448178</ref>與[[丹尼索瓦人|丹尼索瓦人]]<ref>^ Reich D, Green RE, Kircher M, et al.（December 2010）. "Genetic history of an archaic hominin group from Denisova Cave in Siberia". Nature 468 (7327): 1053–60. doi:10.1038/nature09710. PMID 21179161.</ref>的基因體排序也顯示確實發生某些混雜。在非洲以外的現代人類在其基因體中，有2-4％的尼安德塔人的[[等位基因|等位基因]]，[[美拉尼西亞|美拉尼西亞]]人額外具有4-6％的丹尼索瓦人等位基因。這些新的結果並不與《源出非洲》模型相抵觸，但顯示發生了一些額外的混雜事件。可能源自於距今73,000年前的[[多峇巨災理論|多峇超級火山災難]]的一個[[種群瓶頸|種群瓶頸]]之後，經過一段復甦時間，一支很小的群體離開非洲，並遇到尼安德塔人，可能是在中東，他們的後代擴散到世界各地，有一小支遇到了丹尼索瓦人，可能是在東南亞，就在他們遷入美拉尼西亞之前。<ref>Reich D ., et al. Denisova admixture and the first modern human dispersals into southeast Asia and oceania. Am J Hum Genet. 2011 Oct 7;89（4）:516-28, PMID 21944045 .</ref>

